General notice
Based on Article 13 of the Swiss Federal Constitution and the provisions of Swiss federal data protection legislation (Federal Act on Data Protection, FADP), every person has a right to privacy and protection against the misuse of their personal data. The operator of this website takes the protection of your personal data very seriously. We treat your personal data confidentially and in accordance with data privacy requirements as well as this privacy notice.
In collaboration with our hosting providers, we endeavor to protect the databases against unauthorized access, losses, misuse and falsification as effectively as possible.
Note that the transmission of data via the internet (e.g. when communicating by email) may be subject to security vulnerabilities. It is not possible to fully protect data against access by third parties.
By using this website, you declare that you agree with the collection, processing and use of data in accordance with the following provisions. In general, this website can be visited without registering. When you visit our website, data is stored on the server for statistical purposes. This data may include the pages visited or the names of accessed files, and the date and time, and cannot be connected directly to you. Personal data, in particular, your name, address and email address, is collected on a voluntary basis to the extent possible. Data will not be shared with third parties without your consent.
Privacy notice for cookies
This website uses cookies. Cookies are small text files that make it possible to store specific information related to the user on the user’s end device while they use the website. In particular, cookies enable us to determine the user frequency and number of users of the pages, to analyze user behavior while using the pages, and to make our offering more customer-friendly. Cookies remain stored after the end of the browser session and can be accessed again when the site is visited again. If you do not want this to happen, you can adjust your internet browser settings to reject cookies.
A general objection to the use of cookies used for online marketing purposes can be submitted via a number of service providers, especially, in the case of tracking, at the US website
http://www.aboutads.info/choices/
and the EU website
http://www.youronlinechoices.com/
. In addition, the storage of cookies can be deactivated by disabling cookies in your browser settings. Please note that if you so, you may not be able to use all of the functionalities of this online offering.
Privacy notice for SSL/TLS encryption
This website uses SSL/TLS encryption for security reasons and to protect the transmission of confidential content, such as inquiries that you send to us as the website operator. You can recognize an encrypted connection when you see “http://” in the address bar of your browser change to “https://” and the lock symbol is displayed in your browser bar.
When SSL or TLS encryption is activated, third parties cannot read the data that you transmit to us.
Privacy notice for the contact form
When you send us inquiries via the contact form, we save your information from the contact form, including the contact details you provide there to process the inquiry and for follow-up questions. We do not share this data without your consent.
Privacy notice for newsletter data
If you would like to receive the newsletter offered on this website, we need an email address from you as well as information that allows us to confirm that you are the owner of the email address specified by you and that you agree to receive the newsletter. No other data is collected. We use this data solely to send the requested information and we do not share it with third parties.
You can revoke your consent to the storage of data and your email address and its use to send the newsletter at any time, by using the unsubscribe link in the newsletter, for example.
Google Ads
This website uses Google conversion tracking. If you access our website by clicking on a Google ad, Google Ads stores a cookie on your computer. The conversion tracking cookie is stored when a user clicks on an ad delivered by Google. These cookies expire after 30 days and are not used for personal identification purposes. If a user visits certain pages on our website and the cookie has not yet expired, we and Google will be able to see that the user has clicked on the ad and was forwarded to this page. Each Google Ads customer receives a different cookie. As a result, cookies cannot be tracked across the websites of Ads customers. The information collected using conversion cookies is used to compile conversion statistics for Ads customers who have opted for conversion tracking. Customers learn the total number of users who have clicked on their ads and were forwarded to a site with a conversion tracking tag. However, they do not receive any information that can be used to personally identify users.
If you do not wish to participate in tracking, you can reject the corresponding cookie – for example, via the browser setting that automatically deactivates the storage of cookies, or by setting up your browser so that cookies from the domain “googleadservices.com” are blocked.
Please note that the opt-out cookies cannot be deleted if you do not want data to be recorded. If you delete all of the cookies in your browser, you will have to set the opt-out cookie again.
Use of Google remarketing
This website uses the Google Inc. remarketing function. This function is used to provide website visitors within the Google ad network with interest-based advertising. A cookie is saved in the visitor’s browser, which makes it possible to recognize the visitor when they access the website affiliated with the Google ad network. Visitors to these websites can be shown ads that relate to content the visitor accessed previously on websites that use the Google remarketing function.
Google states that it does not collect any personal data during this process. However, if you do not want to enable the Google remarketing function, you can generally deactivate it by adjusting the corresponding settings at
http://www.google.com/settings/ads
. Alternatively, you can disable the use of cookies for interest-based advertising via the advertising network initiative by following the instructions at
http://www.networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp
.
Use of Google reCAPTCHA
This website uses the reCAPTCHA service offered by Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street Dublin 4, Ireland (“Google”). The query is used to distinguish whether an entry was made by a human or by automated machine processing. The query involves the submission of the IP address and, where applicable, other data required for the reCAPTCHA service to Google. For this purpose, your entry is sent to Google and used further there. However, your IP address is first truncated by Google within member states of the European Union or in other states that are party to the Agreement on the European Economic Area. The full IP address will only be transmitted to a Google server in the US and truncated there in exceptional cases. On behalf of the operator of this website, Google will use this information to analyze your use of this service. The IP address transmitted from your browser as part of the reCAPTCHA service will not be combined with other Google data. Your data may also be transmitted to the US. A European Union adequacy decision (“Privacy Shield”) has been obtained for the transmission of data to the US. Google participates in the Privacy Shield and is subject to its requirements. By entering a response, you consent to your data being processed. The processing is carried out on the basis of Article 6(1)(a) GDPR with your consent. You can revoke your consent at any time without affecting the lawfulness of the processing carried out on the basis of the consent prior to revocation.
Further details about Google reCAPTCHA and the related privacy policy can be found at:
https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en
Privacy policy for Google Analytics
This website uses Google Analytics, a web analysis service of Google Ireland Limited. If the controller for data processing on this website is outside the European Economic Area or Switzerland, then the Google Analytics data processing is carried out by Google LLC. Google LLC and Google Ireland Limited are hereafter referred to as “Google”.
The resulting statistics enable us to improve our offering and make it more interesting for you as the user. This website also uses Google Analytics for a cross-device analysis of visitor flows, which is carried out via a user ID. If you have a Google user account, you can deactivate the cross-device analysis of your use of the website in the settings under “My Data”, “Personal Data”.
The legal basis for the use of Google Analytics is Article 6(1)(f) GDPR. The IP address transmitted from your browser as part of the Google Analytics service will not be combined with other Google data. Please note that the code “_anonymizeIp();” has been added to Google Analytics on this website to anonymize users’ IP addresses. As a result, IP addresses are processed after being truncated and it is no longer possible to assign them to a specific person. If there is a personal reference in the data that is collected, it will immediately be excluded and the personal data will be deleted right away.
The full IP address will only be transmitted to a Google server in the US and truncated there in exceptional cases. On behalf of the operator of this website, Google will use this information to analyze your use of the website, to compile reports about website activities and to provide other services to the website operator related to the use of the website and the internet. In the exceptional cases where data is transmitted to the US, Google is subject to the EU-US Privacy Shield,
https://www.privacyshield.gov/EU-US-Framework
.
Google Analytics uses cookies. The information collected by the cookie about your use of this website is generally transmitted to a Google server in the US and stored there. You can prevent the cookies from being stored by adjusting your browser settings; please note, however, that if you do so, you may not be able to make full use of all of the functionalities of this website. You can also prevent Google from storing data generated by the cookie and based on your use of the website (including your IP address) and processing this data by downloading and installing the browser plugin available via the following link:
Disable Google Analytics
.
You can also prevent the use of Google Analytics by clicking on this link:
Disable Google Analytics
. Doing so will store an opt-out cookie on your device that prevents the processing of personal data by Google Analytics. Please note that if you delete all of the cookies on your device, you will also delete this opt-out cookie, i.e. you will have to set the opt-out cookie again if you want to continue to prevent this form of data collection. Opt-out cookies are set for each browser and computer/device and must therefore be activated separately for each browser, computer or other device.
Newsletter – Mailchimp
The newsletter is sent via the provider Mailchimp, a newsletter mailing platform of US provider Rocket Science Group, LLC, 675 Ponce De Leon Ave NE #5000, Atlanta, GA 30308, USA. The service provider’s privacy policy can be found
here
. The Rocket Science Group LLC d/b/a Mailchimp is certified under the Privacy Shield agreement and thus guarantees that the European level of data protection will be observed (
Privacy Shield
). The service provider is used on the basis of our legitimate interests in accordance with Article 6(1)(f) GDPR and a processing contract in accordance with Article 28(3) GDPR.
The service provider can use the recipient’s data in pseudonymized form, i.e. without allocating it to a user, to optimize or improve its own services, e.g. for the technical optimization of the mailing and presentation of the newsletter or for statistical purposes. However, the service provider does not use the data of our newsletter recipients to contact them or to share the data with third parties.
